Fill and boil your #kettle{}. Halve the @green chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed and finely
chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Pour the boiling
water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat, add @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to
the boil.

Add the @spaghetti{180%g}, bring to the boil and cook for ~{8%minutes}. When the pasta
is cooked, reserve @reserved pasta water{100%ml} then drain the spaghetti into a
#colander{}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the
@British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} and a pinch of chilli and cook, stirring, until
the bacon lardons are golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the @king prawns{150%g}, cook for
~{2%minutes}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw meat and prawns. Cook
lardons thoroughly. Add the garlic and mix through. Cook for another ~{1%minute}.

Add the reserved pasta water to the sauce with the @vegetable stock paste{10%g}.
Mix well to dissolve the stock. Turn the heat to low and add the
@creme fraiche{150%g}. Stir and simmer until the prawns are cooked through and the
sauce is piping hot, another ~{2-3%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when
pink on the outside and opaque in the centre.

Stir the drained pasta into your sauce and gently mix. If you feel the sauce needs
loosening up, add a splash of water. Season to taste with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

Serve the pasta in #bowls{} and finish with a sprinkle of the remaining chilli.
Tuck in! Enjoy!